                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>« <a href="/news-03-2020">March 2020</a> | <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="/news-04-2020">April 2020</a></span> | <a href="/news-05-2020">May 2020</a> »</strong></p>
</div>
<div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;">
<p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p>
</div>



<p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p>
<h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>Many of the SCP wikis celebrated April 1st. On the English wiki many SCP pages changed their colors and turned into <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/april-fools-2020">Super Cool Plants</a>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>On the ZH wiki, The Darkroom 2020 Event of the Mobile Task Forces has concluded. 11 authors submitted 8 SCPs and 4 tales featuring MTFs which are eligible for secret prizes.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>The Spanish-speaking wiki finally made it to 200 unique SCP articles and thus held the SCP-ES-200 contest. 9 authors submitted 7 articles, but only one took home the prize of being labeled ES-200.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>The Czech branch's <a href="http://scp-cs.wikidot.com/cz-contest-iv-hub">Fourth Contest</a> ended on April 30th. Contestants wrote for the theme &quot;Czech Foundation&quot;, with submitted articles showing a bit of the history of the Czech branch.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/wanderers-depths-contest">Wanderers Depths Contest</a> on the Wanderers' Library wiki began this month. A writing contest based on works that take place on or under the Seven Seas (or anything related to the Maritime).</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>The Russian branch SCP-RU has announced its 14th contest - <a href="http://scpfoundation.net/loneliness-and-oblivion-contest">The Isolation Contest</a> in which contestants have to either work with the theme of quarantine or large-scale loss of memories in their articles.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-5554">SCP-5554</a> - (&quot;Aki Aki! 🍊🐻&quot;) - &quot;<em>SCP-5554 is an account under the name &quot;Akihikoteddybear&quot; on the social media platform Instagram.</em>&quot; Written by Mew-ltiverse</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/true-trans-soul-rebel">True Trans Soul Rebel</a> - &quot;<em><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">It's just life.</span></em>&quot; Written by NatVoltaic</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/acquisitions-hub">Acquisitions - a Marshall, Carter &amp; Dark Tale</a> - &quot;<em>My dear fellow, nothing in this world is off-limits.</em>&quot; Written by SRegan</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/ooo-ooo-ooo-ooo-ooo-ooo-ooo">Ooo ooo ooo ooo, ooo ooo ooo</a> - &quot;<em>Cowboy Hephaestus and the Fuck Patrol advanced through the desert sands, keeping low to the ground, their muzak pistols clutched tight.</em>&quot; Written by Tanhony</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/are-we-gentrified-yet">Are We Gentrified Yet?</a> - &quot;<em>Look, you have a show coming up, right? Let me loan you my private collection for one, and for two, U of SoHo loves the place.</em>&quot; Written by UraniumEmpire</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/grant-request-for-a-replacement-keyboard-because-the-caps-lo">GRANT REQUEST FOR A REPLACEMENT KEYBOARD BECAUSE THE CAPS LOCK ON THIS ONE IS BROKEN</a> <tt>[Prometheus Labs]</tt> - &quot;<em>-Sent from my iPhone</em>&quot; Written by Weryllium</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Reviewer's Spotlight Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-3741">SCP-3741</a> - (&quot;The World Is Your Oyster&quot;) - &quot;<em>SCP-3741 is a phenomenon that is currently exhibited by 29 eastern oysters, but may extend to a small quantity of wild oysters.</em>&quot; Written by TheMightyMcB, selected by <em>TheMightyMcB</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2589">SCP-2589</a> - (&quot;Don't Leave Me This Way&quot;) - <em>SCP-2589 only physically consumed an individual if it was assisted.</em> Written by Faminepulse, selected by <em>ihp</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-1193">SCP-1193</a> - (&quot;Buried Giant&quot;) - &quot;<em>SCP-1193-01 is a genetically normal human arm of unusual length, located in a drainage pipe inside the basement of a telephone switching station in Scottsdale, Arizona.</em>&quot; Written by ophite, selected by <em>Crashington</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-3758">SCP-3758</a> - (&quot;The Last Dodo&quot;) - &quot;<em>Due to the fact that SCP-3758-B emits 12,000 roentgens per hour of ionizing radiation from its skin, exact measurements have proven impractical.</em>&quot; Written by daveyoufool, selected by <em>Schumacher</em></li>
</ul>
